# Day 26: Build a Scalable Web Application with Auto Scaling on AWS

## Participant Details

- **Name:**RajiyaShaik
- **Task Completed:**

Deployed EC2 instances to run your web application.

Used security groups to allow HTTP/HTTPS traffic to your instances.

Set up an ELB to distribute incoming traffic between  EC2 instances.

Created an Auto Scaling group to manage EC2 instances dynamically.

Defined scaling policies based on metrics like CPU utilization or incoming traffic.

Implemented CloudWatch monitoring to track the performance of your EC2 instances and ELB.




